t however he was a liar and told the estimator false information although i cannot blame the clientele that safety insurers entirely upon them i can blame them for how they handle a claim from one of their nondrivers i specifically asked the claims adjuster if he needed pictures from the accident to expedite the claim on his side in case there was a dispute he told me we outsource that to an estimator and it is their drivers word against mine on damages so he would not need pictures when i got an estimate i asked the claims adjuster for next steps he told me to take it to an auto body shop to get fix and we will repair the damages i went to the auto body shop they agreed with the estimate from the assessors and that i would need to go through the insurance company for the rental upon doublechecking the rental policy with safety i found that they said they where  liable complete nonsense i then had to send them pictures of the skid marks pictures of the sites and pictures of the damages with my story pointbypoint the claims adjuster could have saved me a lot of time by just telling me that they found me  liable when i asked him about next steps they are an insurance company who practices are dubious to say the least if you get hit by one of their drivers make sure you call the police if the police will not showup take detailed pictures of the accident and car safety will do what ever they can not to pay you if i could give  stars i would thankfully i dont have safety insurance however a client of theirs caused a car accident with me  months ago and after the audacity of claiming it wasnt the drivers fault and sending the case to arbitration and ultimately losing im still waiting to get reimbursed for my outofpocket expenses the the person on my case at safety was matt kelly and he has ignored my emails and calls until  weeks ago when he asked his colleague maureen miller to follow up with me now im being ignored by her too when i call either one of them they dont answer nor do they respond to emails so safe to say that safety insurance has terrible customer service heads up  even if im not a current customer of yours you should still provide a high level of service because i could one day decide to switch providers not now of course but im also not recommending you to any friends or family my experience with safety has been frustrating my claim adjuster never answers his phone or replies to my emails what kind of adjuster doesnt respond to clients i had to speak to other adjusters to get my problem taken care of i was a long time safety ins customer but because their homeowners ins rates were climbing i decided to switch insurers i found a new agency and safety was notified of the swtch and so was my bank everything was done properly a full month before my policy with safety expired it has been a year since the switch and safety will not let me go they have continued to bill me for the first potion of that year despite the fact that noone authorized it i have called written and checked to be sure that the bank didnt somehow authorize a continued policy through safety noone at all authorized the continuation of a duly cancelled policy yet safety refuses to stop billing me everyone else got the notification in a timely manner of the new insurer and safety did too do not ever contract with safety unless you want a lifetime of harrassment for a bill you never made and do not owe safety insurance claimed this business has been claimed by the owner or a representative learn more  reviews details  opens a popup rating details home  rental insurance auto insurance edit  opens a popup edit categories write a review add photo share  opens a popup bookmark  opens a popup transit information show less blue aquarium station  mi blue orange state st station  mi blue green government center station  mi get directions swap startend points start from start from swap startend points safety insurance  custom house st boston ma  get directions edi