 way youre going to immediate service is if you pull a move out of alec baldwins playbook and go berserk on twitter and facebook its funny how quickly they can magically locate your account and address your problems when in a public forum their business policies are questionable at best i am really surprised by the poor reviews here as i had a fantastic experience with safety insurance and lets be honest to be thrilled with how everything worked out after youve rearended someone and crumpled the front end of your car must mean someone else did something right i went directly to the vip claims center in newton  which was still open after pm everyone there was super helpful and friendly thanks don i was able to get a rental car close to my home the very next day although i was given an estimate of two weeks for repairs including a holiday i got daily updates and the car ended up being ready two days early and looked amazing the garage that safety used in needham did a great job i will say that the cost of repairs seemed a bit high and i suspect they may have done more than was absolutely necessary  but  it didnt come out of my pocket and that is the point of insurance overall a really great experience and im sad that i will no longer have them as a provider due to relocation they really came through for me during a stressful event reading some of the other negative reviews gave me pause but i must say i had a positive experience with safety insurance i have a homeowners policy with safety and this past winter the water pipes in my home froze while i was away when i returned home i discovered a water fall rushing from my upstairs bathroom flowing through the upstairs floor cascading into my downstairs kitchen a water supply pipe to my upstairs bath had burst and flooded the house the water may well have been running for days a large portion of my small house was essentially wrecked there wasnt a room that was untouched it was truly a disaster reconstruction took nearly  months however safety was there for me they investigated the claim and the underlying cause  which was traced to a faulty switch in my furnace they appraised the damage and paid the full cost of replacement  which was substantial at the end of the day reconstruction and temporary living costs approached six figures throughout the ordeal my claims representative was patient professional and responsive i admit there were some nervous moments early on while i awaited the results of the claim investigation but in the end safety came through and fullfilled their commitment moreover i believe their reconstruction estimateappraisal was fair even generous my house had antique quartersawn pine floors they were very expensive to replace and yet safety stepped up and paid the full cost they also paid the full replacement cost for my custom kitchen cabinets and appliancesand all the rest yeah it was a huge ordeal something i never ever want to go through again but for me safety insurance saved the day they did in a professional and timely manner what an insurance company is designed to do protect me from a huge financial loss as the result of a catastrophic event well done safety and thanks ive used safety since  or so my girlfriend and i both have auto policies with them and a home owners policy ive had to use the auto policy two times and the claims were processed without issue i will say the adjuster was difficult to reach but the body shop got paid my vehicle was fully repaired in a timely manner so i have nothing really bad to say thankfully i havent had to use the homeowners policy my brother has used them for a homeowners claim and there were no problems stay far far away from this company they are only kind to customers when there is another insurance company involved where they could get a reimbursement if your car is involved in a hit and run forget it  dont even bother reporting it to them my vehicle was hit while parked and my claim was denied because there was paint underneath the headlight where i was hit and they think it is latex paint from a fixed object and the appraiser they hired stated that the light broke in a different why so that means it was on when the car was damaged that is completely impossible when i was at work all day they do not want to pay because they cant get reimbursement from another insurance as they would in a regular accident i have been a customer for years paid on time and only filed one claim  and i wasnt even driving the car in that previous accident i will fight this till the end because i know that they want to avoid paying out and i will bring this to court if i have to never do business with safety insurance if you are on the road pray that you are not hit by one of their drivers although safety insurance will move your claim along quickly they will fail to keep you up to date on their personal action to one of your claims i was actually hit by one of their drivers the man swore he was an honest person and told me that i was in his blind spot however he was a liar and told the estimator false information although i cannot blame the clientele that safety insurers entirely upon them i can blame them for how they handle a claim from one of their nondrivers i specifically asked the claims adjuster if he needed pictures from the accident to expedite the claim on his side in case there was a dispute he told me we outsource that to an estimator and it is their drivers word against mine on damages so he would not need pictures when i got an estimate i asked the claims adjuster for next steps he told me to take it to an auto body shop to get fix and we will repair the damages i went to the auto body shop they agreed with the estimate from the assessors and that i would need to go through the insurance company for the rental upon doublechecking the rental policy with safety i found that they said they where  liable complete nonsense i then had to send them pictures of the skid marks pictures of the sites and pictures of the damages with my story pointbypoint the claims adjuster could have saved me a lot of time by just telling me that they found me  liable when i asked him about next steps they are an insurance company who practices are dubious to say the least if you get hit by one of their drivers make sure you call the police if the police will not showup take detailed pictures of the accident and car safety will do what ever they can not to pay you if i could give  stars i would thankfully i dont have safety insurance however a client of theirs caused a car accident with me  months ago and after the audacity of claiming it wasnt the drivers fault and sending the case to arbitration and ultimately losing im still waiting to get reimbursed for my outofpocket expenses the the person on my case at safety was matt kelly and he has ignored my emails and calls until  weeks ago when he asked his colleague maureen miller to follow up with me now im being ignored by her too when i call either one of them they dont answer nor do they respond to emails so safe to say that safety insurance has terrible customer service heads up  even if im not a current customer of yours you should still provide a high level of service because i could one day decide to switch providers not now of course but im also not recommending you to any friends or family my experience with safety has been frustrating my claim adjuster never answers his phone or replies to my emails what kind of adjuster doesnt respond to clients i had to speak to other adjusters to get my problem taken care of i was a long time safety ins customer but because their homeowners ins rates were climbing i decided to switch insurers i found a new agency and safety was notified of the swtch and so was my bank everything was done properly a full month before my policy with safety expired it has been a year since the switch and safety will not let me go they have continued to bill me for the first potion of that year de