be honest to be thrilled with how everything worked out after youve rearended someone and crumpled the front end of your car must mean someone else did something right i went directly to the vip claims center in newton  which was still open after pm everyone there was super helpful and friendly thanks don i was able to get a rental car close to my home the very next day although i was given an estimate of two weeks for repairs including a holiday i got daily updates and the car ended up being ready two days early and looked amazing the garage that safety used in needham did a great job i will say that the cost of repairs seemed a bit high and i suspect they may have done more than was absolutely necessary  but  it didnt come out of my pocket and that is the point of insurance overall a really great experience and im sad that i will no longer have them as a provider due to relocation they really came through for me during a stressful event reading some of the other negative reviews gave me pause but i must say i had a positive experience with safety insurance i have a homeowners policy with safety and this past winter the water pipes in my home froze while i was away when i returned home i discovered a water fall rushing from my upstairs bathroom flowing through the upstairs floor cascading into my downstairs kitchen a water supply pipe to my upstairs bath had burst and flooded the house the water may well have been running for days a large portion of my small house was essentially wrecked there wasnt a room that was untouched it was truly a disaster reconstruction took nearly  months however safety was there for me they investigated the claim and the underlying cause  which was traced to a faulty switch in my furnace they appraised the damage and paid the full cost of replacement  which was substantial at the end of the day reconstruction and temporary living costs approached six figures throughout the ordeal my claims representative was patient professional and responsive i admit there were some nervous moments early on while i awaited the results of the claim investigation but in the end safety came through and fullfilled their commitment moreover i believe their reconstruction estimateappraisal was fair even generous my house had antique quartersawn pine floors they were very expensive to replace and yet safety stepped up and paid the full cost they also paid the full replacement cost for my custom kitchen cabinets and appliancesand all the rest yeah it was a huge ordeal something i never ever want to go through again but for me safety insurance saved the day they did in a professional and timely manner what an insurance company is designed to do protect me from a huge financial loss as the result of a catastrophic event well done safety and thanks ive used safety since  or so my girlfriend and i both have auto policies with them and a home owners policy ive had to use the auto policy two times and the claims were processed without issue i will say the adjuster was difficult to reach but the body shop got paid my vehicle was fully repaired in a timely manner so i have nothing really bad to say thankfully i havent had to use the homeowners policy my brother has used them for a homeowners claim and there were no problems stay far far away from this company they are only kind to customers when there is another insurance company involved where they could get a reimbursement if your car is involved in a hit and run forget it  dont even bother reporting it to them my vehicle was hit while parked and my claim was denied because there was paint underneath the headlight where i was hit and they think it is latex paint from a fixed object and the appraiser they hired stated that the light broke in a different why so that means it was on when the car was damaged that is completely impossible when i was at work all day they do not want to pay because they cant get reimbursement from another insurance as they would in a regular accident